A FIRE which gutted a disused primary school is being investigated by police.
 More than 30 firefighters tackled the blaze at the former Hopefield Primary School in Bonnyrigg, Midlothian. 
 Fire crews were called at 10.20pm on Sunday and took more than four hours to bring the flames under control. 
Inspector Caroline Mackay said: “This fire has caused extensive damage to the building and will most probably result in its demolition.
“The cause of the fire is still to be established and an initial investigation by Scottish Fire and Rescue Service will be undertaken.
 “Anyone with information, or anyone who was in the vicinity of Hopefield Primary School on Sunday night, is asked to contact police immediately.” 
